#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:13(title)
msgid "Other Useful Applications"
msgstr "Autres programmes utiles"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:15(para)
msgid ""
"There are many very useful applications developed by the Ubuntu Server Team, "
"and others that are well integrated with Ubuntu Server Edition, that might "
"not be well known. This chapter will showcase some useful applications that "
"can make administering an Ubuntu server, or many Ubuntu servers, that much "
"easier."
msgstr ""
"Il existe de nombreuses applications utiles développées par l'équipe serveur "
"d'Ubuntu, bien intégrées dans l'édition serveur d'Ubuntu, qui peuvent être "
"méconnues. Ce chapitre va décrire certaines de ces applications pouvant "
"largement faciliter l'administration d'un ou plusieurs serveurs Ubuntu."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:23(title)
msgid "Update MOTD"
msgstr "Mettre à jour MOTD (message du jour)"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:25(para)
msgid ""
"When logging into an Ubuntu server you may have noticed the informative "
"Message Of The Day (MOTD). This information is obtained and displayed using "
"a couple of packages:"
msgstr ""
"Lorsque vous ouvrez une session sur un serveur Ubuntu, vous avez sans doute "
"remarqué le message du jour (MOTD : Message Of The Day). Cette information "
"est obtenue et affichée grâce à ces quelques paquets :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:32(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>landscape-common:</emphasis> provides the core libraries of "
"<application>landscape-client</application>, which can be used to manage "
"systems using the web based <emphasis>Landscape</emphasis> application. The "
"package includes the <application>/usr/bin/landscape-sysinfo</application> "
"utility which is used to gather the information displayed in the MOTD."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>landscape-common:</emphasis> fournit les bibliothèques "
"essentielles pour <application>landscape-client</application>, qui peut être "
"utilisé pour gérer les systèmes avec l'application en mode Web "
"<emphasis>Landscape</emphasis>. Ce paquet fournit l'application "
"<application>/usr/bin/landscape-sysinfo</application> qui est utilisée pour "
"recueillir l'information affichée par MOTD."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:40(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>update-motd:</emphasis> is used to automatically update the MOTD "
"via <application>cron</application>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>update-motd :</emphasis> permet de mettre à jour MOTD "
"automatiquement grâce à <application>cron</application>."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:46(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>update-motd</application> utility has several options to "
"further customize the MOTD:"
msgstr ""
"L'utilitaire <application>update-motd</application> possède plusieurs "
"options pour personnaliser MOTD :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:52(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>--disable:</emphasis> prevents automatic updates of the MOTD. "
"Using this option creates the <filename>/var/lib/update-"
"motd/disabled</filename> file, which if present stops <application>update-"
"motd</application> from modifying <filename>/etc/motd</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>--disable :</emphasis> empêche les mises à jour automatiques de "
"MOTD. L'utilisation de cette option crée le fichier "
"<filename>/var/lib/update-motd/disabled</filename>. Si ce fichier existe "
"<application>update-motd</application> ne peut plus modifier "
"<filename>/etc/motd</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:59(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>--enable:</emphasis> enables the automatic MOTD updates. If "
"<filename>/var/lib/update-motd</filename> is present it will be removed."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>--enable :</emphasis> active les mises à jour automatiques de "
"MOTD. Si le fichier <filename>/var/lib/update-motd</filename> existe, il "
"sera supprimé."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:65(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>--force:</emphasis> does a one time update of "
"<filename>/etc/motd</filename>, overriding <application>update-"
"motd</application> if it has been disabled."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>--force :</emphasis> met à jour une seule fois "
"<filename>/etc/motd</filename>,  en prenant le pas sur <application>update-"
"motd</application> si il a été désactivé."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:71(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>d, hourly, weekly, monthly:</emphasis> option will run the scripts "
"in <filename>/etc/update-motd.d/</filename> (default), <filename>/etc/update-"
"motd.d/hourly</filename>, <filename>/etc/update-motd.d/weekly</filename>, or "
"<filename>/etc/update-motd.d/monthly</filename> respectively."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>d, hourly, weekly, monthly :</emphasis> exécute les scripts "
"présents dans <filename>/etc/update-motd.d/</filename> (par défault), "
"<filename>/etc/update-motd.d/hourly</filename>, <filename>/etc/update-"
"motd.d/weekly</filename>, ou <filename>/etc/update-motd.d/monthly</filename> "
"respectively."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:79(para)
msgid ""
"<application>update-motd</application> executes the scripts in "
"<filename>/etc/update-motd.d</filename> in order based on the number "
"prepended to the script. Separate <application>cron</application> scripts "
"execute every ten minutes, hourly, weekly, and monthly running the "
"corresponding scripts in <filename>/etc/update-motd.d</filename>. The output "
"of the scripts is written to <filename>/var/run/update-motd/</filename>, "
"keeping the numerical order, then concatenated with "
"<filename>/etc/motd.tail</filename> and written to "
"<filename>/etc/motd</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<application>update-motd</application> exécute les scripts présents dans "
"<filename>/etc/update-motd.d</filename> dans l'ordre défini par le nombre "
"qui préfixe le nom du script. Les scripts individuels "
"<application>cron</application> lancent toutes les 10 minutes, toutes les "
"heures, les semaines ou les mois, les scripts correspondants dans "
"<filename>/etc/update-motd.d</filename>. Les messages de sortie de ces "
"scripts sont écrits dans <filename>/var/run/update-motd/</filename>, dans "
"l'ordre numérique, puis concaténés avec <filename>/etc/motd.tail</filename> "
"et écrits dans <filename>/etc/motd</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:87(para)
msgid ""
"You can add your own dynamic information to the MOTD. For example, to add "
"local weather information:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez ajouter des informations dynamiques au message du jour (MOTD). "
"Par exemple, pour ajouter la météo locale :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:93(para)
msgid "First, install the <application>weather-util</application> package:"
msgstr "Installez d'abord le paquet <application>weather-util</application>"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:98(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install weather-util"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install weather-util"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:103(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>weather</application> utility uses METAR data from the "
"National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration and forecasts from the "
"National Weather Service. In order to find local information you will need "
"the 4-character ICAO location indicator. This can be determined by browsing "
"to the <ulink url=\"http://www.weather.gov/tg/siteloc.shtml\">National "
"Weather Service</ulink> site."
msgstr ""
"Le programme <application>weather</application> utilise les données METAR de "
"la National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration et les prévisions du "
"National Weather Service. Pur avoir les informations locales, vous aurez "
"besoin de l'indicateur à 4 caractères du lieu désiré. Vous pouvez le trouver "
"en cherchant sur le site <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.weather.gov/tg/siteloc.shtml\">National Weather "
"Service</ulink>"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:110(para)
msgid ""
"Although the National Weather Service is a United States government agency "
"there are weather stations available world wide. However, local weather "
"information for all locations outside the U.S. may not be available."
msgstr ""
"Bien que le National Weather Service soit une agence gouvernementale "
"américaine, il y a des stations météo disponibles pour le monde entier. "
"Cependant, toutes les informations météorologiques en dehors des États-Unis "
"ne sont pas forcement disponibles."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:116(para)
msgid ""
"Create <filename>/usr/local/bin/local-weather</filename>, a simple shell "
"script to use <application>weather</application> with your local ICAO "
"indicator:"
msgstr ""
"Créez <filename>/usr/local/bin/local-weather</filename>, simple script shell "
"pour utiliser <application>weather</application> avec votre indicateur :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:121(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"##########################################################################\n"
"#\n"
"# Prints the local weather to /var/run/update-motd/60-local-weather  \n"
"# for update-motd.\n"
"#\n"
"##########################################################################\n"
"\n"
"# Replace KINT with your local weather station.\n"
"# Local stations can be found here: http://www.weather.gov/tg/siteloc.shtml\n"
"\n"
"echo \"\" &gt; /var/run/update-motd/60-local-weather\n"
"weather -i KINT &gt;&gt; /var/run/update-motd/60-local-weather\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"##########################################################################\n"
"#\n"
"# Inscrit la météo locale dans /var/run/update-motd/60-local-weather  \n"
"# pour mettre à jour MOTD.\n"
"#\n"
"##########################################################################\n"
"\n"
"# Remplacez KINT avec votre indicateur.\n"
"# Chercher votre station sur : http://www.weather.gov/tg/siteloc.shtml\n"
"\n"
"echo \"\" &gt; /var/run/update-motd/60-local-weather\n"
"weather -i KINT &gt;&gt; /var/run/update-motd/60-local-weather\n"
"\n"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:139(para)
msgid "Make the script executable:"
msgstr "Rendez le script exécutable :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:144(command)
msgid "sudo chmod 755 /usr/local/bin/local-weather"
msgstr "sudo chmod 755 /usr/local/bin/local-weather"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:148(para)
msgid ""
"Next, create a symlink to <filename>/etc/update-motd.d/60-local-"
"weather</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Ensuite, créez un lien symbolique vers <filename>/etc/update-motd.d/60-local-"
"weather</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:153(command)
msgid ""
"sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/local-weather /etc/update-motd.d/60-local-weather"
msgstr ""
"sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/local-weather /etc/update-motd.d/60-local-weather"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:157(para)
msgid "Finally, update the MOTD:"
msgstr "Pour finir, mettez à jour MOTD :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:162(command)
msgid "sudo update-motd"
msgstr "sudo update-motd"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:167(para)
msgid ""
"You should now be greeted with some useful information, and some information "
"about the local weather that may not be quite so useful. Hopefully the "
"<application>local-weather</application> example demonstrates the "
"flexibility of <application>update-motd</application>."
msgstr ""
"Vous devriez avoir des informations de la météo locale dans le MOTD. Ceci "
"n'est qu'un exemple vous montrant la flexibilité de <application>update-"
"motd</application>."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:175(title)
msgid "etckeeper"
msgstr "etckeeper"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:177(para)
msgid ""
"<application>etckeeper</application> allows the contents of <filename "
"role=\"directory\">/etc</filename> be easily stored in Version Control "
"System (VCS) repository. It hooks into <application>apt</application> to "
"automatically commit changes to <filename>/etc</filename> when packages are "
"installed or upgraded. Placing <filename>/etc</filename> under version "
"control is considered an industry best practice, and the goal of "
"<application>etckeeper</application> is to make this process as painless as "
"possible."
msgstr ""
"<application>etckeeper</application> permet de garder une trace des "
"modifications effectuées dans <filename role=\"directory\">/etc</filename> "
"en le plaçant dans un dépôt CVS. Il interagit avec "
"<application>apt</application> pour appliquer les changements "
"automatiquement à  <filename>/etc</filename> lorsque des paquets sont "
"installés ou mis à jour. Mettre <filename>/etc</filename> sous contrôle de "
"version est considéré comme étant une bonne pratique par la profession et le "
"but de <application>etckeeper</application> est de rendre le processus aussi "
"aisé que possible."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:185(para)
msgid ""
"Install <application>etckeeper</application> by entering the following in a "
"terminal:"
msgstr ""
"Installez <application>etckeeper</application> en tapant dans un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:190(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install etckeeper"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install etckeeper"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:193(para)
msgid ""
"The main configuration file, "
"<filename>/etc/etckeeper/etckeeper.conf</filename>, is fairly simple. The "
"main options being which VCS and which package management system to use. By "
"default <application>etckeeper</application> is configured to use "
"<application>bzr</application> for version control, "
"<application>apt</application> for high level package mangement, and "
"<application>dpkg</application> for low level package management."
msgstr ""
"Le fichier de configuration principal, "
"<filename>/etc/etckeeper/etckeeper.conf</filename>, est relativement simple. "
"Les options principales concernent le CVS et le système de gestion de "
"paquets à utiliser. Par défaut <application>etckeeper</application> est "
"paramétré pour utiliser <application>bzr</application> comme CVS, "
"<application>apt</application> pour la gestion avancée de paquets et "
"<application>dpkg</application> pour la gestion simple de paquets."

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:200(para)
msgid ""
"With the package installed, it is time to initialize the repository. In a "
"terminal enter:"
msgstr ""
"Le paquet installé, il est temps d'initialiser le dépôt. Saisissez dans un "
"terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:205(command)
msgid "sudo etckeeper init"
msgstr "sudo etckeeper init"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:208(para)
msgid "Next, commit the files to the repository:"
msgstr "Ensuite, transférez les fichiers dans le dépôt :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:213(command)
msgid "sudo etckeeper commit \"initial import\""
msgstr "sudo etckeeper commit \"initial import\""

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:216(para)
msgid ""
"Using the VCS commands you can view log information about files in "
"<filename>/etc</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez voir le journal des fichiers de <filename>/etc</filename> en "
"utilisant les commandes CVS :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:221(command)
msgid "sudo bzr log /etc/passswd"
msgstr "sudo bzr log /etc/passswd"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:224(para)
msgid ""
"To demonstrate the integration with the package management system, install "
"<application>postfix</application>:"
msgstr ""
"Pour vérifier l'intégration avec le système de gestion de paquets, installez "
"<application>postfix</application> :"

#: serverguide/C/other-apps.xml:229(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:38(command)
