#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:682(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>Mailman</application>, run following command at a "
"terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Pour installer <application>Mailman</application>, lancez la commande "
"suivante dans un terminal:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:686(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install mailman"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install mailman"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:688(para)
msgid ""
"It copies the installation files in "
"<application>/var/lib/mailman</application> directory. It installs the CGI "
"scripts in <application>/usr/lib/cgi-bin/mailman</application> directory. It "
"creates <emphasis>list</emphasis> linux user. It creates the "
"<emphasis>list</emphasis> linux group. The mailman process will be owned by "
"this user."
msgstr ""
"Il copie les fichiers d'installation dans le répertoire "
"<application>/var/lib/mailman</application>. Il installe les scripts CGI "
"dans le répertoire <application>/usr/lib/cgi-bin/mailman</application>. Il "
"crée l'utilisateur Linux <emphasis>list</emphasis>. Il crée le groupe Linux "
"<emphasis>list</emphasis>. Le processus mailman appartiendra à cet "
"utilisateur."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:700(para)
msgid ""
"This section assumes you have successfully installed "
"<application>mailman</application>, <application>apache2</application>, and "
"<application>postfix</application> or <application>exim4</application>. Now "
"you just need to configure them."
msgstr ""
"Cette section suppose que vous avez installé "
"<application>mailman</application>, <application>apache2</application>, and "
"<application>postfix</application> or <application>exim4</application> avec "
"succès. Maintenant vous devez juste les configurer."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:709(para)
msgid ""
"An example Apache configuration file comes with "
"<application>Mailman</application> and is placed in "
"<filename>/etc/mailman/apache.conf</filename>. In order for Apache to use "
"the config file it needs to be copied to <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-"
"available</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Un exemple de fichier de configuration pour Apache est livré avec "
"<application>Mailman</application> et placé dans "
"<filename>/etc/mailman/apache.conf</filename>. Pour qu'Apache utilise le "
"fichier de configuration, il devra être copié vers "
"<filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:715(command)
msgid ""
"sudo cp /etc/mailman/apache.conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/mailman.conf"
msgstr ""
"sudo cp /etc/mailman/apache.conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/mailman.conf"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:717(para)
msgid ""
"This will setup a new Apache <emphasis>VirtualHost</emphasis> for the "
"Mailman administration site. Now enable the new configuration and restart "
"Apache:"
msgstr ""
"Ceci configurera un nouvel <emphasis>VirtualHost</emphasis> d'Apache pour le "
"site d'administration de Mailman. À présent, activez la nouvelle "
"configuration et redémarrez Apache :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:722(command)
msgid "sudo a2ensite mailman.conf"
msgstr "sudo a2ensite mailman.conf"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:725(para)
msgid ""
"Mailman uses apache2 to render its CGI scripts. The mailman CGI scripts are "
"installed in the <application>/usr/lib/cgi-bin/mailman</application> "
"directory. So, the mailman url will be http://hostname/cgi-bin/mailman/. You "
"can make changes to the <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-"
"available/mailman.conf</filename> file if you wish to change this behavior."
msgstr ""
"Mailman utilise apache2 pour exécuter ses scripts CGI. Les scripts CGI de "
"Mailman sont installés dans le répertoire <application>/usr/lib/cgi-"
"bin/mailman</application>. Donc, l'url de mailman sera http://hostname/cgi-"
"bin/mailman/.. Vous pouvez modifier le fichier de configuration "
"<filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/mailman.conf</filename> si vous "
"souhaitez changer ce comportement."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:736(para)
msgid ""
"For <application>Postfix</application> integration, we will associate the "
"domain lists.example.com with the mailing lists. Please replace "
"<emphasis>lists.example.com</emphasis> with the domain of your choosing."
msgstr ""
"Pour l'intégration de <application>Postfix</application>, nous associerons "
"le domaine lists.example.com avec les listes de diffusion. Veuillez "
"remplacer <emphasis>lists.example.com</emphasis> par le domaine de votre "
"choix."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:740(para)
msgid ""
"You can use the postconf command to add the necessary configuration to "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez utiliser la commande postconf pour ajouter les configurations "
"nécessaires à <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:744(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'relay_domains = lists.example.com'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'relay_domains = lists.example.com'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:745(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'transport_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/transport'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'transport_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/transport'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:746(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'mailman_destination_recipient_limit = 1'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'mailman_destination_recipient_limit = 1'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:748(para)
msgid ""
"In <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> double check that you have "
"the following transport:"
msgstr ""
"Dans <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename>, vérifiez bien que vous "
"avez le transport suivant :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:751(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"mailman   unix  -       n       n       -       -       pipe\n"
"  flags=FR user=list argv=/usr/lib/mailman/bin/postfix-to-mailman.py\n"
"  ${nexthop} ${user}\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"mailman   unix  -       n       n       -       -       pipe\n"
"  flags=FR user=list argv=/usr/lib/mailman/bin/postfix-to-mailman.py\n"
"  ${nexthop} ${user}\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:756(para)
msgid ""
"It calls the <emphasis>postfix-to-mailman.py</emphasis> script when a mail "
"is delivered to a list."
msgstr ""
"Il appelle le script <emphasis>postfix-to-mailman.py</emphasis> quand un "
"courriel est destiné à une liste de diffusion."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:759(para)
msgid ""
"Associate the domain lists.example.com to the Mailman transport with the "
"transport map. Edit the file <filename>/etc/postfix/transport</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Associez le nom de domaine lists.example.com au transport Mailman grâce au "
"transport map. Modifiez le fichier "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/transport</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:762(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"lists.example.com      mailman:\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"lists.example.com      mailman:\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:765(para)
msgid ""
"Now have <application>Postfix</application> build the transport map by "
"entering the following from a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"À présent, faites construire la carte de transport par "
"<application>Postfix</application> en saisissant ceci dans un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:769(command)
msgid "sudo postmap -v /etc/postfix/transport"
msgstr "sudo postmap -v /etc/postfix/transport"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:771(para)
msgid "Then restart Postfix to enable the new configurations:"
msgstr ""
"Ensuite redémarrez Postfix pour activer les nouvelles configurations :"

