#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1011(title)
msgid "Mail Filtering"
msgstr "Filtrage du courrier éléctronique"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1012(para)
msgid ""
"One of the largest issues with email today is the problem of Unsolicited "
"Bulk Email (UBE). Also known as SPAM, such messages may also carry viruses "
"and other forms of malware. According to some reports these messages make up "
"the bulk of all email traffic on the Internet."
msgstr ""
"L'un des plus gros problèmes avec le courrier électronique à l'heure "
"actuelle sont les courriers électroniques non sollicités envoyés en masse  "
"(ou UBE en anglais). Également connus sous le nom de SPAM, ces messages "
"peuvent également transmettre des virus et d'autres formes de logiciels "
"malveillants. Selon certains rapports, ces messages constituent l'essentiel "
"de l'ensemble du trafic e-mail sur Internet."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1017(para)
msgid ""
"This section will cover integrating <application>Amavisd-new</application>, "
"<application>Spamassassin</application>, and "
"<application>ClamAV</application> with the "
"<application>Postfix</application> Mail Transport Agent (MTA). "
"<application>Postfix</application> can also check email validity by passing "
"it through external content filters. These filters can sometimes determine "
"if a message is spam without needing to process it with more resource "
"intensive applications. Two common filters are <application>dkim-"
"filter</application> and <application>python-policyd-spf</application>."
msgstr ""
"Cette section va couvrir l'intégration de <application>Amavisd-"
"new</application>, <application>Spamassassin</application>, et "
"<application>ClamAV</application> avec le Mail Transport Agent (MTA ou "
"logiciel pour serveur de transmission de courriers électroniques) "
"<application>Postfix</application>. <application>Postfix</application> peut "
"aussi vérifier la validité des emails en les faisant passer au travers de "
"filtres de contenu externes. Ces filtres peuvent parfois déterminer si un "
"message est du courrier indésirable (spam) sans avoir à le traiter avec des "
"applications plus gourmandes en ressources. Deux filtres communs sont "
"<application>dkim-filter</application> et <application>python-policyd-"
"spf</application>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1027(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Amavisd-new</application> is a wrapper program that can call "
"any number of content filtering programs for spam detection, antivirus, etc."
msgstr ""
"<application>Amavisd-new</application> est un programme enveloppe qui peut "
"appeler différents programmes de filtrage de contenu pour la détection de "
"courrier indésirable (spam), anti-virus, etc."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1033(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Spamassassin</application> uses a variety of mechanisms to "
"filter email based on the message content."
msgstr ""
"<application>Spamassassin</application> utilise divers mécanismes pour "
"filtrer les courriers en se basant sur leur contenu."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1038(para)
msgid ""
"<application>ClamAV</application> is an open source antivirus application."
msgstr "<application>ClamAV</application> est anti-virus libre."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1043(para)
msgid ""
"<application>dkim-filter</application> implements a Sendmail Mail Filter "
"(Milter) for the DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) standard."
msgstr ""
"<application>dkim-filter</application> implémente un filtre mail Sendmail "
"(Milter) pour le standard DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM)."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1049(para)
msgid ""
"<application>python-policyd-spf</application> enables Sender Policy "
"Framework (SPF) checking with <application>Postfix</application>."
msgstr ""
"<application>python-policyd-spf</application> active la vérification Sender "
"Policy Framework (SPF) avec <application>Postfix</application>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1054(para)
msgid "This is how the pieces fit together:"
msgstr "Voici comment ces applications collaborent :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1059(para)
msgid "An email message is accepted by <application>Postfix</application>."
msgstr "Un courriel est accepté par <application>Postfix</application>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1064(para)
msgid ""
"The message is passed through any external filters <application>dkim-"
"filter</application> and <application>python-policyd-spf</application> in "
"this case."
msgstr ""
"Le message est passé par tout les filtres externes <application>dkim-"
"filter</ application> et <application>python-policyd-spf</ application> dans "
"le cas présent."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1070(para)
msgid "<application>Amavisd-new</application> then processes the message."
msgstr "<application>Amavisd-new</application> traite ensuite le message."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1075(para)
msgid ""
"<application>ClamAV</application> is used to scan the message. If the "
"message contains a virus <application>Postfix</application> will reject the "
"message."
msgstr ""
"<application>ClamAV</application> est utilisé pour nalyser le message. Si le "
"message contient un virus alors <application>Postfix</application> le "
"rejettera."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1081(para)
msgid ""
"Clean messages will then be analyzed by "
"<application>Spamassassin</application> to find out if the message is spam. "
"<application>Spamassassin</application> will then add X-Header lines "
"allowing <application>Amavisd-new</application> to further manipulate the "
"message."
msgstr ""
"Les messages propres seront ensuite analysés par "
"<application>Spamassassin</application> pour savoir si le courrier est "
"indésirable (spam). <application>Spamassassin</application> ajoutera alors "
"des lignes X-Header permettant à <application>Amavisd-new</application> de "
"manipuler le message par la suite."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1088(para)
msgid ""
"For example, if a message has a Spam score of over fifty the message could "
"be automatically dropped from the queue without the recipient ever having to "
"be bothered. Another, way to handle flagged messages is to deliver them to "
"the Mail User Agent (MUA) allowing the user to deal with the message as they "
"see fit."
msgstr ""
"Par exemple, si un message a un score Spam de plus de cinquante le message "
"pourrait être automatiquement sorti de la file sans que le destinataire ne "
"soit jamais embêté. Un autre moyen de traiter les messages signalés est de "
"les remettre au client de messagerie électronique (MUA) autorisant "
"l'utilisateur à gérer le message comme il le souhaite."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1095(para)
msgid ""
"See <xref linkend=\"postfix\"/> for instructions on installing and "
"configuring Postfix."
msgstr ""
"Consultez <xref linkend=\"postfix\"/> pour les instructions d'installation "
"et de configuration de Postfix."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1098(para)
msgid ""
"To install the rest of the applications enter the following from a terminal "
"prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Pour installer le reste des applications saisissez ce qui suit dans un "
"terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1102(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install amavisd-new spamassassin clamav-daemon"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install amavisd-new spamassassin clamav-daemon"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1103(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install dkim-filter python-policyd-spf"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install dkim-filter python-policyd-spf"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1105(para)
msgid ""
"There are some optional packages that integrate with "
"<application>Spamassassin</application> for better spam detection:"
msgstr ""
"Il existe des paquets facultatifs qui s'intègrent avec "
"<application>Spamassassin</application> pour une meilleure détection des "
"spams :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1109(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install pyzor razor"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install pyzor razor"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1111(para)
msgid ""
"Along with the main filtering applications compression utilities are needed "
"to process some email attachments:"
msgstr ""
"Avec les principales applications de filtrage, des utilitaires de "
"compression sont nécessaires pour traiter certaines pièces jointes :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1115(command)
msgid ""
"sudo apt-get install arj cabextract cpio lha nomarch pax rar unrar unzip zip "
"zoo"
msgstr ""
"sudo apt-get install arj cabextract cpio lha nomarch pax rar unrar unzip zip "
"zoo"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1120(para)
msgid "Now configure everything to work together and filter email."
msgstr ""
"Configurez maintenant cela pour que tou fonctionne ensemble et flitre les "
"courriers."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1124(title)
msgid "ClamAV"
msgstr "ClamAV"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1125(para)
msgid ""
"The default behaviour of <application>ClamAV</application> will fit our "
"needs. For more ClamAV configuration options, check the configuration files "
"in <filename>/etc/clamav</filename>."
msgstr ""
"L'installation par défaut de <application>ClamAV</application> nous "
"conviendra. Regardez son fichier de configuration dans "
"<filename>/etc/clamav</filename> pour avoir accès à plus d'options."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1130(para)
msgid ""
"Add the <emphasis>clamav</emphasis> user to the <emphasis>amavis</emphasis> "
"group in order for <application>Amavisd-new</application> to have the "
"appropriate access to scan files:"
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez l'utilisateur <emphasis>clamav</emphasis> au groupe "
"<emphasis>amavis</emphasis> de manière à ce que <application>Amavisd-"
"new</application> ait les droits suffisants pour lire les fichiers :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1135(command)
msgid "sudo adduser clamav amavis"
msgstr "sudo adduser clamav amavis"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1139(title)
msgid "Spamassassin"
msgstr "Spamassassin"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1140(para)
msgid ""
"Spamassassin automatically detects optional components and will use them if "
"they are present. This means that there is no need to configure "
"<application>pyzor</application> and <application>razor</application>."
msgstr ""
"Spamassassin détecte automatiquement les composants supplémentaires et les "
"utilisera s'ils sont présents. Ceci veut donc dire qu'il n'est pas "
"nécessaire de configurer <application>pyzor</application> et "
"<application>razor</application>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1144(para)
msgid ""
"Edit <filename>/etc/default/spamassassin</filename> to activate the "
"<application>Spamassassin</application> daemon. Change "
"<emphasis>ENABLED=0</emphasis> to:"
msgstr ""
"Modifiez <filename>/etc/default/spamassassin</filename> pour activer le "
"démon <application>Spamassassin</application>. Changez "
"<emphasis>ENABLED=0</emphasis> par :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1148(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"ENABLED=1\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"ENABLED=1\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1151(para)
msgid "Now start the daemon:"
msgstr "Lancez maintenant le démon :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1155(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/spamassassin start"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/spamassassin start"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1159(title)
msgid "Amavisd-new"
msgstr "Amavisd-new"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1160(para)
msgid ""
"First activate spam and antivirus detection in <application>Amavisd-"
"new</application> by editing <filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/15-"
"content_filter_mode</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"D'abord, activez la détection de spam et de virus dans <application>Amavisd-"
"new</application> en éditant <filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/15-"
"content_filter_mode</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1164(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"use strict;\n"
"\n"
"# You can modify this file to re-enable SPAM checking through spamassassin\n"
"# and to re-enable antivirus checking.\n"
"\n"
"#\n"
"# Default antivirus checking mode\n"
"# Uncomment the two lines below to enable it\n"
"#\n"
"\n"
"@bypass_virus_checks_maps = (\n"
"   \\%bypass_virus_checks, \\@bypass_virus_checks_acl, \\"
"$bypass_virus_checks_re);\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"#\n"
"# Default SPAM checking mode\n"
"# Uncomment the two lines below to enable it\n"
"#\n"
"\n"
"@bypass_spam_checks_maps = (\n"
"   \\%bypass_spam_checks, \\@bypass_spam_checks_acl, \\"
"$bypass_spam_checks_re);\n"
"\n"
"1;  # insure a defined return\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"use strict;\n"
"\n"
"# You can modify this file to re-enable SPAM checking through spamassassin\n"
"# and to re-enable antivirus checking.\n"
"\n"
"#\n"
"# Default antivirus checking mode\n"
"# Uncomment the two lines below to enable it\n"
"#\n"
"\n"
"@bypass_virus_checks_maps = (\n"
"   \\%bypass_virus_checks, \\@bypass_virus_checks_acl, \\"
"$bypass_virus_checks_re);\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"#\n"
"# Default SPAM checking mode\n"
"# Uncomment the two lines below to enable it\n"
"#\n"
"\n"
"@bypass_spam_checks_maps = (\n"
"   \\%bypass_spam_checks, \\@bypass_spam_checks_acl, \\"
"$bypass_spam_checks_re);\n"
"\n"
"1;  # insure a defined return\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1189(para)
msgid ""
"Bouncing spam can be a bad idea as the return address is often faked. "
"Consider editing <filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/20-debian_defaults</filename> "
"to set <emphasis>$final_spam_destiny</emphasis> to D_DISCARD rather than "
"D_BOUNCE, as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Le renvoi d'un spam à l'expéditeur peut être une mauvaise idée étant donné "
"que l'adresse de retour est souvent fausse. Vous devriez modifier "
"<filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/20-debian_defaults</filename> pour configurer "
"<emphasis>$final_spam_destiny</emphasis>sur D_DISCARD plutôt que D_BOUNCE, "
"comme suit :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1194(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"$final_spam_destiny       = D_DISCARD;\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"$final_spam_destiny       = D_DISCARD;\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1198(para)
msgid ""
"If the server's <emphasis>hostname</emphasis> is different from the domain's "
"MX record you may need to manually set the <emphasis>$myhostname</emphasis> "
"option. Also, if the server receives mail for multiple domains the "
"<emphasis>@local_domains_acl</emphasis> option will need to be customized. "
"Edit the <filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/50-user</filename> file:"
msgstr ""
"Si le <emphasis>nom d'hôte (hostname)</emphasis> du serveur est différent de "
"l'enregistrement MX du domaine vous devrez fixer vous-même l'option "
"<emphasis>$myhostname</emphasis>. De même, si le serveur sert de multiples "
"domaines, l'option <emphasis>@local_domains_acl</emphasis> devra être "
"personnalisée. Modifiez le fichier <filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/50-"
"user</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1205(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"$myhostname = 'mail.example.com';\n"
"@local_domains_acl = ( \"example.com\", \"example.org\" );\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"$myhostname = 'mail.example.com';\n"
"@local_domains_acl = ( \"example.com\", \"example.org\" );\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1210(para)
msgid ""
"After configuration <application>Amavisd-new</application> needs to be "
"restarted:"
msgstr ""
"Après sa configuration, <application>Amavisd-new</application> doit être "
"redémarré :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1214(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:1260(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/amavis restart"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/amavis restart"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1217(title)
msgid "DKIM Whitelist"
msgstr "Liste blanche DKIM"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1219(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Amavisd-new</application> can be configured to automatically "
"<emphasis>Whitelist</emphasis> addresses from domains with valid Domain "
"Keys. There are some pre-configured domains in the "
"<filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/40-policy_banks</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<application>Amavisd-new</application> peut être configuré pour mettre "
"automatiquement les adresses des domaines ayant des clés correctes en "
"<emphasis>liste blanche</emphasis>. Des domaines pré configurés se trouvent "
"dans <filename>/etc/amavis/conf.d/40-policy_banks</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1225(para)
msgid "There are multiple ways to configure the Whitelist for a domain:"
msgstr ""
"Il existent plusieurs manières de configurer la liste blanche d'un domaine :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1231(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>'example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis>: will whitelist any "
"address from the \"example.com\" domain."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>'example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis> : ajoute toutes les "
"adresses du domaine « example.com » à la liste blanche ."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1236(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>'.example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis>: will whitelist any "
"address from any <emphasis>subdomains</emphasis> of \"example.com\" that "
"have a valid signature."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>'.example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis> : ajoute n'importe "
"quelle adresse de n'importe quel <emphasis>sous-domaine</emphasis> de "
"« example.com » s'ils ont une signature valable."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1242(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>'.example.com/@example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis>: will "
"whitelist subdomains of \"example.com\" that use the signature of <emphasis "
"role=\"italic\">example.com</emphasis> the parent domain."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>'.example.com/@example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis> : ajoute "
"les sous-domaines de « example.com » qui utilisent la signature du domaine "
"parent <emphasis role=\"italic\">example.com</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1248(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>'./@example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis>: adds addresses "
"that have a valid signature from \"example.com\". This is usually used for "
"discussion groups that sign thier messages."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>'./@example.com' =&gt; 'WHITELIST',</emphasis> : ajoute les "
"adresses ayant une signature valable issue de « example.com ». Ceci est "
"généralement utilisé pour les groupes de discussions signant leur messages."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1255(para)
msgid ""
"A domain can also have multiple Whitelist configurations. After, editing the "
"file restart <application>amaisd-new</application>:"
msgstr ""
"Un domaine peut avoir de multiples configurations de liste blanche. "
"Redémarrez <application>amavisd-new</application> pour prendre en compte les "
"modifications :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1264(para)
msgid ""
"In this context, once a domain has been added to the Whitelist the message "
"will not receive any anti-virus or spam filtering. This may or may not be "
"the intended behavior you wish for a domain."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce contexte, une fois qu'un domaine a été ajouté à la liste blanche, le "
"message ne sera pas filtré par un anti-virus quelconque ou un anti-spam. "
"Ceci peut ne pas vous convenir."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1274(para)
msgid ""
"For <application>Postfix</application> integration, enter the following from "
"a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Pour l'intégration dans <application>Postfix</application>, saisissez la "
"commande suivant dans un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1278(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'content_filter = smtp-amavis:[127.0.0.1]:10024'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'content_filter = smtp-amavis:[127.0.0.1]:10024'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1280(para)
msgid ""
"Next edit <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> and add the following "
"to the end of the file:"
msgstr ""
"Ouvrez ensuite le fichier <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> et "
"ajoutez ce qui suit tout à la fin :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:1283(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp-amavis     unix    -       -       -       -       2       smtp\n"
"        -o smtp_data_done_timeout=1200\n"
